  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6814.92 sitting right between massive negative gamma walls at 6810-6815 (-78B to -58B) and positive gamma resistance at 6830 (+23B), dealers are caught in aggressive short-gamma hedging mode - they're buying this dip but will flip to selling any bounce toward 6830. The -20.8% GEX surge with wall breaks detected suggests we're in a volatile amplification zone where dealer flows will accelerate moves in both directions rather than provide cushioning. Watch 6810 as the critical support where maximum negative gamma forces dealers into momentum buying, while 6830 represents the ceiling where they'll aggressively sell rallies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect whippy, amplified moves between 6810-6830 with dealers adding fuel to whatever direction breaks first.",
